Regex to find problematic usages of str.format()...

{code}
[^u]['"].+['"].format\(
{code}

A simple fix for this would be to leverage Python 3's unicode-by-default string formatting via...

{code}
from __future__ import unicode_literals
{code}

With that import in the module, u'foo' and 'foo' should be equivalent.

Note: modules that include the import must include a UTF-8 encoding stanza at the top of the module...

{code}
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
{code}

See http://python-future.org/unicode_literals.html
